metadata.name: EDDY #257
metadata.description:
An eddy is a circular movement of water counter to a main current. It reminds me of innovations in art, like a small countercurrent to the mainstream, surfacing new techniques and aesthetics. 

I hope that EDDY will brighten your days with its playful swirl of colors, inspired by the sea, the sky, the birds, and post-impressionist paintings.

Keyboard Controls:
[F] Fill the window.
[S] Save the current view in live mode as an image (default 1125x1500px).
[1] [2] [4] [6] Change resolution, 1.5K to 9K.
[R] Reverse course.

Made with p5js and shaders.

Created by elsif, 2022.12.

metadata.name: Misunderstanding #296
metadata.description:
Each color/stripe represents a single person or a group of people, trying to communicate with each other. But their attempts in an understandable and agreeable communication are mostly always misaligned. Hence, none of them understand each other as they want to be understood. And for that, some of them don't even bother trying to communicate at all.

* * *

Happy anniversary! #fxhashturnsone

Press S to save as PNG. To save a larger image, open live view, add "&s=WIDTH_IN_PIXELS" to the end of the URL, press Enter and then press S.

Artwork by: yenren / twitter.com/yenrenART
License: NFT License 2.0 / CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: Wildwood Forest #18
metadata.description:
The Trees are the embodiment of a sanctorium. Anyone who knows how to speak to them and listen to them can embrace the truth. they preach the ancient law of life. Under these trees bushes that generate the flow of life in the darkened celestial sphere , with the greatest sun of spring's clear weather and again in fall when every leaf is a flower. And what magnificent bouquets the autumn leaves make.

Enjoy :)

metadata.name: 空-sora- #302
metadata.description:
Japanese word Sora(空) means Sky.

An abstract painting of a landscape with sky.
Drawing based on mathematics fractal.

Top has 3 variations.
Bottom has 4 variations.
Cloud has 3 variations.
Background has White or Black 2 variations.
Stroke has ON or OFF 2 variations.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [f] to switch full screen on and off
- Press [s] to download a PNG file with windowsize
- Press [l] to download a PNG file with large size 3200 x 4800 pixel (wait a minutes)

Create with p5.js
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Generative Fantasies: 101 Compositions #56
metadata.description:
This could be a follow-up to Herbert W. Franke's finding of interesting connections between Constructivism and Generative art, where at first, technological limits allowed only simple line drawings, based on fixed proportions, and later were extended by the use of random generators. Constructivism, as an art movement, sought to depict modern civilization, the symbiotic relationship between technology and art, industrialization, and urban spaces. Iakov Chernikhov (Яков Чернихов), an architect and graphic artist, was one of the influential figures in Constructivism. He extensively used the two-point perspective with an observation point below the ground in his drawings. 

In this (my) exploration of two-point perspective, random, colorful, and glassy constructions visual resemblance to Chernikhov’s oeuvre is inescapable. Therefore the title is a play on the original title of his book Architectural Fantasies: 101 Compositions in Color, 101 Architectural Miniatures from 1933.

The subtle grain effect is done with p5.grain library by Gorilla Sun (@gorillasu) & meezwhite (@meezwhite). 

Look out for the FOMO keyboard key to unlock more variations.

metadata.name: In Due Time #164
metadata.description:
“In Due Time” is a collaborative generative collection between artists Melissa Wiederrecht and Amber Vittoria. Inspired by Wiederrecht’s mastery of line and Vittoria’s notable palette, this 1/1/250 series captures the present moment. It serves as a reminder that we are more similar than we are different, leveraging homogeneous shapes to create distinctive compositions.

Vittoria’s poem for the collection:

“In Due Time”
We will all become
Particles dancing
Across the skyline.

The artwork listed is indeed authentic, created by, and copyright to artists Melissa Wiederrecht and Amber Vittoria; the purchase of this NFT is a purchase of the asset, not of the copyright.

-------------------------------------------

To save a high-resolution image for printing, click “open” under the image on the page for your token, and then hit:

Digits “1” through “9” to get an image that is 1000 through 9000px tall.  This may take a while, depending on the size and your computer, so please be patient.

metadata.name: Let's Celebrate #12
metadata.description:
All peoples have established anniversaries to celebrate their victories, disorders, or misfortunes.
Having said that, people are social beings, and you cannot celebrate whatever it may be alone. So join those who are celebrating 
their success because they will join you in celebrating yours when the time comes. Then, as you praise and celebrate your life, 
there will be more life to enjoy. For all of the humans out there, remember that celebrations don't have to revolve around grandiose 
things. It's okay to celebrate a simple life. However, for all of us pursuing our passions, remember that although celebrating 
achievement is significant, learning from failure is much more crucial. while you cherish the milestones as you prepare for the road 
ahead.

Fxhash turns one, Happy birthday !

---
Created using vanilla javascript
KrouniHatim - Nov22
---
(CC BY-ND 4.0)

metadata.name: Curlida #188
metadata.description:
Fully generative art. Each token is 100% unique.

Traits:
- 28 color palettes;
- 5 "stylers" - cells filling style;
- 3 "ratio" - aspect ratio.

Press 's' to save png.

High-level description of the algorithm:
Frame is separated into flows using several different Perlin noise generators. 
Frame cells are filled with curves. Each curve is drawn in the direction plotted by noise generator.
Each value returned by the generator at (x, y) is mapped to color from a predefined range.


Made with p5js, math and love by @ivposure

metadata.name: Twistings #15
metadata.description:
✧ TWISTINGS ✧

Twistings, the "Explore Variety" collection, explores the beauty & variety that is hidden within the simple math of Archimedean spirals.

There are seven different circular "entities", each brought forward by using slightly different mathematical settings of the spiral formulas: Drops, Circles, Fireworks, Flowers, Roses, Spirals & Twisters.

____

✧ CURATED / RANDOM ✧

I love both the concept of a heavily curated set, hand picked by the artist, the best representation / the most beautiful, but also the concept of the larger, random collections showing the variety hidden within the algorithm.

I've therefore also released an "Artist Curated" collection of 7 pieces that I meticulously hand-picked from over 1000 outputs. You can find these on the platform 1stDibs.com/nft (under my name "nadieh"). They represent my favorite for each of the seven unique entities. A free mint of this "Explore Variety" collection will be airdropped to each buyer of a "Curated" piece.

____

✧ OPTIONS ✧

n - Toggle grainy noise on/off (on by default, it's subtle to see)

s - Save the image at the current window size and pixel density

To save a larger image you can add the parameter `&pixeldensity=2` (or another number) to the end of the URL when viewed on the live page. Afterwards press "s" to save the image. The number is the factor with which the width and height are increased w.r.t. the current window size.

-- The larger the image / pixeldensity, the longer it will take to create & save --

____

✧ NOTES ✧

It works best and fastest in Firefox!

As of the drop day there is a browser bug for Chrome on the ARM Apple laptops. It incorrectly visualizes certain color blend modes. The following color palettes are affected: Antique, Camping, Pastel, Prime & Rainbow. I hope/assume this will be fixed soon. 

____

Created by Nadieh Bremer
Twitter & Instagram: @NadiehBremer
Website: VisualCinnamon.com
